- [.] Install Python (3.10+ recommended)
- [.] Install Flask (pip install flask)
- [.] Install SQLite (comes built-in with Python, but confirm with: python -c "import sqlite3")
- [.] Create project folder structure:
      project/
        app.py
        templates/
        static/
          css/
          images/
        db/
          fruit.db
- [ ] Initialize SQLite DB (sqlite3 db/fruit.db)
- [ ] Create tables (countries, fruit_facts) in DB
- [ ] Insert a few sample rows (e.g., Japan, Brazil, Mexico with fruit facts)
- [ ] Write app.py with a minimal Flask "Hello World" route
- [ ] Add Flask route /country/<slug> to query DB and render a template
- [ ] Create templates/country.html with placeholders ({{ country.name }}, {{ facts }})
- [ ] Test /country/japan loads from DB correctly
- [ ] Add Flask route /random-country that returns a random country from DB
- [ ] Hook astronaut image in index.html to fetch /random-country and redirect user
- [ ] Move your existing home.css into static/css/ and link it with:
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('static', filename='css/home.css') }}">
- [ ] Test CSS + Flask template integration
- [ ] Add at least 10 real country entries into DB
- [ ] Verify navigation works between /country/<slug> pages
- [ ] Seed DB with full list of ~100 countries + facts
- [ ] Polish country.html template styling with your existing design
- [ ] Add error handling for missing slugs (404 page)
- [ ] Deploy locally with "flask run" and test all pages
- [ ] (Optional) Deploy to free host (Render, Railway, PythonAnywhere, or Heroku-style service)
